        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 3:26PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 322 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking thunderstorms with heavy
rain along a line extending from near Goshen to near Danby. Movement
was northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Thunderstorms with very heavy rain may lead to ponding of
water on roads and in low lying areas.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Over an inch of rain has been observed in some locations,
and these slow moving storms will lead to additional heavy
rainfall.

Locations impacted include...
Castleton, East Clarendon, Hydeville, Sudbury, Florence, Belmont,
Cuttingsville, Killington, Giffords Woods State Forest Park, Lake St.
Catherine State Park, Rutland City, Middletown Springs, Wallingford,
Mt. Holly, Mt. Tabor, East Pittsford, North Pawlet, Rutland -
Southern Vermont Airport, Poultney, and North Clarendon.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
